1. No wildcard imports (use foo::*) — import specific items by name
2. No TODO/FIXME comments in committed code — create work items instead
3. No inline imports inside function bodies — all use statements at file top
4. No redundant variable bindings — don't bind to a variable just to return it on the next line
5. No duplicate struct fields across types — if Config and DbConfig share host/port/name, embed DbConfig in Config
6. Functions that take a struct as first parameter should be methods on that struct, not free functions
7. No vague function names — do_the_thing, helper_process, etc. must describe what they actually do
